BASS COAST! What a journey. I've played every summer since year 2 and it's been an incredible experience to see it grow and become our home. It is consistently the highlight of my summer to squeeze so much bliss into a set and see the smiles and tears that flow as so many of you resonate with the sounds and emotions. After 10 volumes of the Bliss Coast series I am turning a corner to explore something a little different and so it is with much joy that I can finally share these sounds with you all. Enjoy, as I know you will!

We are so proud to bring you our 68th guest mix episode. This time from the hand of Kid Caravan, the electrifying alter ego of M.E.M.O., a breakbeat pioneer and living legend in Spain. 
At just 16, he began captivating audiences of over 30,000 with his exceptional vinyl skills and innovative blend of scratch techniques and hip-hop influences, becoming a driving force in the genre’s evolution. With a career spanning more than three decades, he has performed alongside electronic music giants at renowned festivals like Creamfields, Dreambeach, Brunch in the Park, and others, while also taking his sound to clubs and events across the globe, from the US and Europe to Asia and Latin America.

Now, as Kid Caravan, M.E.M.O. returns with renewed energy, reconnecting with his breakbeat roots and pushing the genre into new dimensions. Combining innovative approaches, technical mastery, and an unmatched ability to connect with audiences, Kid Caravan represents not only the present but also the future of breakbeat.

When compiling the story of Markus Schulz's career, his connection with the people of Los Angeles, and particularly the legendary venue of Avalon in Hollywood, would require a book-long chapter. A venue in which his dedication to the open to close performance of the DJ art excels, he returned on Saturday February 1 for his latest adventure. A city and area reeling from the devastation caused by forest fires, his goal for the night carried an extra emotion as a result, aiming to provide those affected with a small sense of escape, at least for a little while. 

This set forms part of Markus' monthly Global DJ Broadcast World Tour series - providing a snapshot of his sounds in the liveset envrionment; spread across famed clubs and festivals around the globe. The next will take him to Soundcheck in Washington DC, where he will play on Valentine's Night, Friday February 14. 

You're also welcome to check out Markus' companion 30 minute streaming series Weekly Drive, with the newly released episode 36 out now at https://gdjb.complete.me/weeklydrive36

Y no podemos estar más orgullosos de poder contar con este pedazo de artista ya que es la primera vez que en tu canal favorito de sesiones breaks te traemos un mix que vas a poder disfrutar tanto en audio en nuestra plataforma como en video en el canal de Youtube del propio artista, una nueva idea que me propuso el amigo Müme y que sin duda acepte a la primera porque vais a alucinar tanto con la música en si del set que se ha grabado como con el precioso video que ha preparado cuidadosamente donde podrás disfrutar de todos los detalles que vas a poder oír en el mix. Nuestro participante número 71 tiene ya una más que consagrada posición en la escena ya que ha actuado en los festivales más top de sonidos breakbeat que tenemos ahora mismo en Andalucia, Sesión super divertida y dinámica donde se unen pasión, musicon, y profesionalidad . Vas a poder disfrutar de temas ya a la venta en plataformas diversas y algunos TRACKS inéditos que aún no han visto la luz y que saldrán en muy poquito por labels muy punteros que ya descubriréis cuando el artista lo haga público .
Así que si sabes quién es Müme y te encanta su estilo y si música está es tu sesión.
No dudes en ningún momento en pulsar el botón de play y alucina con la maravilla que nos regala el gran Müme desde Jerez de la frontera.
Amigos y oyentes una vez más gracias por estar ahí y está es la primera pero no la última de las que vamos a ofreceros en formato audio/video.
